Tetris Multiplayer General Commands Manual

NAME
       create-gr - creates a new group in the tetris multiplayer database.

SYNOPSIS
       create-gr [-bprl] [--group-name GROUP_NAME]

DESCRIPTION
       create-gr - creates a new group in the tetris multiplayer database with the specified criteria.

       The following options are available:

	-b
		Sets the ban user permission to true.

	-p
		Sets the post news permission to true. 

	-r
		Sets the reset user data permission to true.

	-l
		Sets the log in to server permission to true.

	--group-name=GROUP_NAME
		Specifies the group name.

EXIT STATUS
    The create-gr command returns true on success (and creates the group) or false if an error occurs.